In the closely divided Senate, it’s more important than ever that we elect Cheri to advocate for affordable health care, voting rights, environmental protections, and job creation.

I’m proud to endorse my friend, Cheri Beasley, for the U.S. Senate. 

Cheri is a trailblazer with a track record in public service as a Judge on the NC of Appeals and as Chief Justice of the NC Supreme Court. We need her voice in Washington, fighting for the people of NC.

➡️Passed two common sense gun violence prevention bills to provide for universal background checks & to close the ‘Charleston Loophole’

Today is #EqualPayDay, marking the date that women, on average, have to work to make the same amount that men made in 2020. Its time to close the wage gap and ensure that women are make equal pay for equal work.

Today the House passed bills to enact universal background checks and close the “Charleston loophole”. I was proud to cosponsor both of these bills and to vote in favor of their passage.
